ou are, it reduces your fear of trials\n\n- Sunday\n|\nFireheart, why do you cry?''Because I am lost. And do not know the way\n\n- Sarah\n|\nCan’t clean up after you anymore, baby brother, so don’t punk out. Make it count.\n\n- Rachel Vincent, Reaper\n|\nJesus does not suffer so as to exclude your suffering. He bears a cross, not that you may escape it, but that you may endure it.\n\n- Charles Haddon Spurgeon, Morning and Evening, Based on the English Standard Version\n|\nA life without love is like a sunless garden when the flowers are dead. So, keep love in your heart if not your best friend today will turn to your worst enemy tomorrow.\n\n- Osunsakin\n|\nThe tough challenges we encounters, makes us stronger, and wiser. With each victory we gain something of value; our character is strengthened.\n\n- Ellen\n|\nIf it is true, as God says, that we are as we think, we risk becoming what we most fear if our fear is stronger than our love.\n\n- Ron\n|\nIn knowledge there is strength, in understanding there is might, and in wisdom there is power.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWhen you will learn to recognize your true self, you will find the true beauty and the magic of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIn the end, what will hurt us the most is not the words of our enemies but the silence of our friends.\n\n- Martin\n|\nHe had to get out, get some space between him and the world, just to breathe.\n\n- Allison\n|\nI have my own matches and sulphur, and I'll make my own hell.\n\n- Rudyard Kipling, The Light That Failed\n|\nChange is hardest at the beginning, messiest in the middle and best at the end.\n\n- Robin S. Sharma, The Leader Who Had No Title: A Modern Fable on Real Success in Business and in Life\n|\nWe are limited by knowledge, not by courage.\n\n- Amit\n|\nThe strength of a man is in his character. A strong man is a great man of wisdom who understands, his top priority is to his family.\n\n- Ellen J. Barrier, The Price We Must Pay for Our Father's Sins\n|\nIf you are ready for the s